<AuHeading @level="3" @skin="3">How To Work With The Decision Data Hive</AuHeading>

<AuHeading @level="4" @skin="4">1. Choose What Type Of Data You Want To Explore</AuHeading>

<p>When local governments publish their linked data, the information gets assigned <strong>types</strong> that you can explore.</p>

<p>Letâ€™s say you want to explore council meetings (zittingen) in the database:</p>
<CodeBlock @code='PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX besluit: <http://data.vlaanderen.be/ns/besluit#>
SELECT * WHERE {
  ?sub a besluit:Zitting.
} LIMIT 10'
  @language="html" />

<p>You can do the same with the decisions (besluiten):</p>
<CodeBlock @code='PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX besluit: <http://data.vlaanderen.be/ns/besluit#>
SELECT * WHERE {
  ?sub a besluit:Besluit.
} LIMIT 10'
  @language="html" />

<p>You can also find out explore who attended a council meeting:</p>

<CodeBlock @code='PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX besluit: <http://data.vlaanderen.be/ns/besluit#>
PREFIX person: <http://www.w3.org/ns/person#>
SELECT * WHERE {
  ?sub a person:Person.
} LIMIT 10'
  @language="html" />

<AuHr @size="large" />
<AuHeading @level="4" @skin="4">2. If desired, adjust the query</AuHeading>
<p>Just like with any other query, you can order the results, count them, set limits,...</p>

<CodeBlock @code='SELECT DISTINCT ?bestuursorgaan (COUNT(?s) AS ?aantalZittingen) WHERE {
  ?s a besluit:Zitting;
    besluit:isGehoudenDoor ?bestuursorgaan.
}
GROUP BY ?bestuursorgaan
ORDER BY ?aantalZittingen'
  @language="html" />

<AuHelpText>This query will show you the amount of meetings in each Governing Body (bestuursorgaan), in ascending order.</AuHelpText>

<p>If you want to discover more types of data you can query on, execute this query and you will find more possibilities:</p>

<CodeBlock @code='SELECT DISTINCT ?type WHERE {
  ?sub a ?type .
} LIMIT 100'
  @language="html" />

